## Climate

Stirling, much like the rest of the [United Kingdom](/United_Kingdom), experiences an [oceanic climate](/Oceanic_climate) ([Köppen](/K%C3%B6ppen_climate_classification) Cfb ), characterized by mild summers and cool, wet winters. Stirling enjoys some of the warmest summers in Scotland, owing to its relative distance from the moderating maritime influences of the [North Sea](/North_Sea) and the [Firth of Clyde](/Firth_of_Clyde).

